Funny, I did that exact thing.  I tried to make the smallest change to
junit.textui.TestRunner I could:

120c120
&lt; failure.thrownException().printStackTrace(writer());
---
&gt; printStackTrace(failure.thrownException());
142c142
&lt; failure.thrownException().printStackTrace(writer());
---
&gt; printStackTrace(failure.thrownException());
146a147,149
&gt; protected void printStackTrace(Throwable t) {
&gt;     t.printStackTrace(writer());
&gt; }

And then this allows me to override printStackTrace() in our custom
TestRunner:

    protected void printStackTrace(Throwable t) {
        StringWriter buffer = new StringWriter(1000);
        t.printStackTrace(new PrintWriter(buffer));
        StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(buffer.toString(), &quot;&#92;r&#92;n&quot;);
        while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
            String line = st.nextToken();
            if (line.indexOf(&quot;at junit.&quot;) == -1)
                writer().println(line);
        }
    }

